\c 86
\s1 Doa yang ditulis oleh Daud
\q1
\v 1 Ya TUHAN, berilah perhatian kepada perkataanku dan jawablah aku,
\q2 sebab aku lemah dan [butuh pertolongan/tidak berdaya].
\q1
\v 2 Peliharalah jiwaku sebab aku melayani-Mu,
\q2 selamatkanlah hamba-Mu, ya TUHAN-ku.
\q1
\v 3 TUHAN, berbuat baiklah kepadaku,
\q2 sebab aku berseru kepada-Mu sepanjang hari setiap hari.
\q1
\v 4 TUHAN, buatlah aku bersukacita,
\q2 sebab aku because I ◄pray to/worship► [IDI] you.
\b
\q1
\v 5 Lord, you are good \add to us\add*, and you forgive us;
\q1 you faithfully love very much all those who ◄pray/call out► to you.
\q1
\v 6 Lord, listen to my prayer;
\q2 hear me when I cry out to you to help me.
\q1
\v 7 When I have troubles, I call out to you,
\q2 because you answer me.
\b
\q1
\v 8 Lord, among all the gods \add whom the heathen nations worship\add*,
\q2 there is no one like you;
\q1 not one of them has done \add the great things\add* that you have done.
\q1
\v 9 Tuhan, semua orang dari suku-suku bangsa di dunia akan datang dan bersujud di hadapan-Mu,
\q2 mereka akan memuji dan menyembah-Mu.
\q1
\v 10 You are great, and you do wonderful/marvelous things;
\q2 only you are God.
\b
\q1
\v 11 Yahweh, teach me what you want me to do
\q2 in order that I may conduct my life according to what you say, which is true.
\q1 Cause/Teach me to have an awesome respect for you with all my inner being.
\q1
\v 12 Lord, my God, I will thank you with all my inner being,
\q2 and I will praise you forever.
\q1
\v 13 You faithfully love me very much;
\q2 you have prevented me from \add dying and going to\add* the place where dead people are.
\b
\q1
\v 14 But God, proud men are \add trying to\add* attack me;
\q2 a gang/group of cruel men are wanting to kill me;
\q2 they are men who do not have any ◄respect for/interest in► you.
\q1
\v 15 But Lord, you always act mercifully and kindly;
\q2 you do not become angry quickly,
\q2 and you faithfully love us very much
\q2 and always do for us what you have promised to do.
\q1
\v 16 Look down toward me and act mercifully to me;
\q2 cause me to be strong and save/rescue me
\q2 who serves you \add faithfully\add* like my mother did.
\q1
\v 17 Yahweh, do something to show me that you are being good to me
\q2 in order that those who hate me will see that you have encouraged me and helped me
\q2 and as a result they will be ashamed.